<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<taxonomicName authorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" baseAuthorityYear="2021" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lychnuris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lychnuris klugii" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lychnuris klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Motschulsky, V" journalOrPublisher="Etudes Entomologiques" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" refId="B38" refString="Motschulsky, V, 1853. Lampyrides (Continuation). Etudes Entomologiques 2: 1.32." title="Lampyrides (Continuation). Etudes Entomologiques 2: 1.32." year="1853">Motschulsky (1853</bibRefCitation>
: 4), who wrongly attributed the species authorship to Dejean. Indeed, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dejean, PFMA" journalOrPublisher="Mequignon-Marvis, Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" refId="B12" refString="Dejean, PFMA, 1833. Catalogue des Coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Mequignon-Marvis, Paris" title="Catalogue des Coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean." year="1833">Dejean (1833)</bibRefCitation>
cited 
<taxonomicName authorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" baseAuthorityYear="2021" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lychnuris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lychnuris klugii" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lychnuris klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in his second catalog, but without a description, making it therefore a 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">nomen nudum</emphasis>
(cf. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.282.4401" author="Bousquet, Y" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" pagination="1 - 219" refId="B6" refString="Bousquet, Y, Bouchard, P, 2013. The genera in the second catalogue (1833-1836) of Dejean's Coleoptera collection. ZooKeys 282: 1 - 219, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.282.4401" title="The genera in the second catalogue (1833 - 1836) of Dejean's Coleoptera collection." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.282.4401" volume="282" year="2013">Bousquet and Bouchard 2013</bibRefCitation>
). The correct authorship of the species belongs to 
<bibRefCitation author="Motschulsky, V" journalOrPublisher="Etudes Entomologiques" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" refId="B38" refString="Motschulsky, V, 1853. Lampyrides (Continuation). Etudes Entomologiques 2: 1.32." title="Lampyrides (Continuation). Etudes Entomologiques 2: 1.32." year="1853">Motschulsky (1853)</bibRefCitation>
, who in first provided a description for 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lychnacris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lychnacris klugii" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lychnacris klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Motschulsky, V" journalOrPublisher="Etudes Entomologiques" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" refId="B38" refString="Motschulsky, V, 1853. Lampyrides (Continuation). Etudes Entomologiques 2: 1.32." title="Lampyrides (Continuation). Etudes Entomologiques 2: 1.32." year="1853">Motschulsky (1853)</bibRefCitation>
lists the species for Southern Brazil, without further details.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<normalizedToken originalValue="McDermott’s">McDermott's</normalizedToken>
catalog (1966) cites Motschulsky, 1853: 28 as a first mention of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" baseAuthorityYear="2021" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lychnuris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lychnuris klugii" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lychnuris klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but this is inaccurate in two ways. On one side, the first citation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" baseAuthorityYear="2021" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lychnuris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lychnuris klugii" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lychnuris klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was indeed on a &quot;page 28&quot;, but in 1852, not 1853. However, we interpret that in 
<bibRefCitation author="Motschulsky, V" journalOrPublisher="Etudes Entomologiques" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" pagination="25 - 58" refId="B37" refString="Motschulsky, V, 1852. Lampyrides. Etudes Entomologiques 1: 25 - 58" title="Lampyrides." volume="1" year="1852">Motschulsky 1852</bibRefCitation>
: 28, 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. klugii" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">L. klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">nomen nudum</emphasis>
, as the synopsis given regards the genus 
<taxonomicName family="Lampyridae" genus="Lychnuris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lychnuris" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lychnuris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1833 (valid 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">fide</emphasis>
Bousquet &amp; Bouchard, 2013), not the species. The correct reference of the species description, as listed above, is Motschulsky, 1853: 4.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2311.1880.tb02016.x" author="Gorham, HS" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" pagination="1 - 36" refId="B21" refString="Gorham, HS, 1880. I. Materials for a revision of the Lampyridae. Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London 28: 1 - 36, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2311.1880.tb02016.x" title="I. Materials for a revision of the Lampyridae." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2311.1880.tb02016.x" volume="28" year="1880">Gorham (1880)</bibRefCitation>
transferred 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Motschoulsky" authorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lychnacris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lychnacris" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lychnacris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lucidota" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lucidota" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lucidota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Laporte, 1833. Since then, it was transferred to 
<taxonomicName family="Lampyridae" genus="Lychnuris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lychnuris" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lychnuris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Olivier, E" journalOrPublisher="Revue scientifique du Bourbonnais et du centre de la France" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" pagination="39 - 58" refId="B46" refString="Olivier, E, 1911. Revision des Lampyrides. Revue scientifique du Bourbonnais et du centre de la France 24: 39 - 58" title="Revision des Lampyrides." volume="24" year="1911">Olivier (1911)</bibRefCitation>
, and back to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lucidota" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lucidota" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lucidota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="McDermott, FA" editor="Steel, WO" journalOrPublisher="Pars 9 (editio secunda). W. Junk, S'Gravenhage" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" pagination="1 - 149" refId="B34" refString="McDermott, FA, 1966. Lampyridae. In: Steel, WO, Ed., , Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementa. Pars 9 (editio secunda). W. Junk, S'Gravenhage: 1 - 149" title="Lampyridae." volumeTitle=", Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementa." year="1966">McDermott (1966)</bibRefCitation>
. After our phylogenetic analysis (see section 3.2), we transfer 
<taxonomicName authorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lucidota" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lucidota klugii" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lucidota klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Motschulsky, 1853) to 
<taxonomicName authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Costalampys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">gen. nov.</emphasis>
, therefore 
<taxonomicName authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1853" baseAuthorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys klugii" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Costalampys klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Motschulsky, 1853) 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<taxonomicName authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1853" baseAuthorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys klugii" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Costalampys klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky, 1853 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">comb. nov.</emphasis>
is very unique among other 
<taxonomicName authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Costalampys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. in lacking an elongate elytral pale-yellow spot. The paired pink vittae usually seen in the pronotum is often found as well in 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. tricolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C. tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Gorham, 1880) 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">comb. nov.</emphasis>
, from which 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. klugii" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C. klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky, 1853 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">comb. nov.</emphasis>
can be distinguished by the lack of an elongate, elytral pale-yellow stripe, and lack of lanterns on sternum VI (both traits present in 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. tricolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C. tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Gorham, 1880) 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">comb. nov.</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
